@startmindmap
* Decision Contracts - Scripting Atlas (Normative)
** Cross-Cutting Evaluator Hook [high]
*** default contract policy applies first
*** optional predicate/evaluator micro-script refines decision at declared hook points
*** evaluator hook points must be explicitly declared by contract (no hidden dynamic hooks)
*** evaluator failures are panic-fast
** File Typing Contracts [very_high]
*** member policy = required | optional | conditional(predicate_fn)
*** file type contract defines required_hooks + optional_hooks with typed signatures
*** phase scope declared in file-type contract metadata by default
** Ctx API Graph [very_high]
*** root ctx is minimal, convenience comes from typed navigable sub-apis
*** capability channels are ctx-graph nodes reachable via typed endpoints
*** read path = snapshot/view handles; write path = intent emission only
*** cross-scale access must pass through explicit gateway (for example ctx.cross_scale)
** Capability Channels [very_high]
*** dependency edge kinds = required | alternative_provider | conflicts_with | enhances
*** reconciliation uses default policies + optional evaluator override where contract allows
*** channel operations are layer-partitioned; cross-layer effects require explicit bridge ops
** Meta Bootstrap [high]
*** multiple meta entrypoints are allowed and executed by an ordered staged plan
*** policy narrowing output = typed allow/deny/bounds graph with deterministic merge order
*** bootstrap emits a machine-readable introspection artifact
** Runtime Orchestration [high]
*** keep coarse global phases and allow typed domain subphases
*** panic-fast is default; sentinel paths are explicit and contract-declared only
** Compile-Time vs Runtime Registration [medium]
*** compile-time owns capability interfaces + hard safety bounds
*** runtime owns script registration, composition, and activation
@endmindmap

@startmindmap
* Residual Uncertainties (Small)
** evaluator hook placement granularity per capability
** metadata format details for bootstrap artifact
** compile-time vs runtime split details for future extension macros
@endmindmap

